25 ancilia] ‘ sacred shields.' The word is derived from amb· and caede, denoting that the shields had two curved indentations in the rim, which

made them like violins in shape. The tradition was that one shield fell ’

from heaven, and eleven more were made exactly like it, that it might not be known and stolen.

The shape of the shield is identical with those of the Mycenaean age, and is perhaps <like the scutum) to be traced to the Pelasgians or Aborigines. The Umbro-Latius had a round shield. Ridgeway, Εανζγ Age qf Greece, 1. p. 455. .
